'''Awanzai''' (Pashto: آعوانزي) is a [[Pashtuns|Pashtun]] allied tribe that resides in [[Afghanistan]] and [[Pakistan]]. 

The [[Awan (tribe)|Awan]] claim Arab descent from Qutb Shah of [[Ghazni]], who ruled at [[Herat]], but joined [[Mahmud of Ghazni]] in his invasions of India in 1004 A.D. and received from him the name of Awanor, which means Helper. Qutb Shah was descended from [[Ali]], the son-in-law of the [[Prophet Muhammad]] but through the [[Family tree of Ali]]'s other wife.
The Awans have been Muslims from the beginning. Qutb Shah had six sons, Kalan Shah, who settled near [[Kalabagh]] while two settled in [[Tirah]] and the [[Kurram Valley]].
The rest settled in Punjab, Pakistan.

The Awans who have been living in the [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] province for centuries have mixed up with other Pashtun tribes like the [[Yousafzai]] tribe in [[Topi, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] which in turn gave birth to a Sub-clan called 'Awanzai'.

On a rural level, Awanzai historically were of the [[zamindar]] or landowning class and many Awanzai families to this day live on and cultivate land, which their ancestors have held for centuries.
{{Citation needed|date=October 2017}}


